On september 2, 2012
SoItBegins

In the vein of Three-Trooper Tourney, I propose a new championship... which takes MiniTroopers to its utmost essence.

ONE-MAN ARMY

Rules

1. Your army may have one, and only one, trooper. Be sure to protect your army with a password so it stays that way!

2. To join, make your army name into a link, followed by your Army Name and player name in ordinary text so that participants know who to challenge. Place this link at the bottom of the list of armies.

Example: http://bimotivality.minitroopers.com/hq Bimotivality / SoItBegins

3. To move up the rank list, beat the person above you (using 'Infiltrate!' in the Pick a Fight section) and post the replay with the updated list.
It is possible to not realize you weren't at the last page, and use an old version of the list. If this happens, please edit your post to fix it!

4. You can have up to two armies per player in the list. You don't fight your own army— you skip over them.

5a. If you want to replace one of your two armies with another, put [RETIRED] next to your retiring army in the list— also, strikethrough the link.

Example: http://bimotivality.minitroopers.com/hq [RETIRED]
Then, you can add your new army at the bottom of the list.

5b. If you want to take a vacation, mark your army [INACTIVE], in the same way. People can skip over INACTIVE armies.

6a. Pilots with a Light Tank or Helicopter are prohibited.

6b. Special rules for vehicle users:
If you attack another army, and your Tank or Helicopter deploys, the match is forfeit.
If you attack another army, and the other guy has a Tank/Helicopter and you win somehow (on foot), it's a justly deserved victory!

7. Have fun!

SoItBegins

doomys, how about changing Rule 6 to the following?

6a. Pilots with a Light Tank or Helicopter are prohibited.

6b. Special rules for vehicle users:
If you attack another army, and your Tank or Helicopter deploys, the match is forfeit.
If you attack another army, and the other guy has a Tank/Helicopter and you win somehow (on foot), it's a justly deserved victory!

Does this sound good?

On september 3, 2012
Kompera
SoItBeginsdoomys, how about changing Rule 6 to the following?
6a. Pilots with a Light Tank or Helicopter are prohibited.

6b. Special rules for vehicle users:
If you attack another army, and your Tank or Helicopter deploys, the match is forfeit.
If you attack another army, and the other guy has a Tank/Helicopter and you win somehow (on foot), it's a justly deserved victory![/qite]

Does this sound good?

Why bother specifying attack? That way there is no need for the second 'if' statement, as the first will cover all situations (except BOTH deploying in a vehicle, but that would probably be rather rare).

It could then read thusly:
If either army deploys in a Tank or Helicopter, that army forfeits the match;

-and perhaps-
If both armies deploy in a vehicle, the winner of the match is awarded the victory.

Guy with a Rifle is also a strong contender despite not being a Saboteur. He is a Soldier with a strong array of defensive items and skills (Heavy Armor, FMB, Tuck'n'roll, Invincible), plus several health increasing skills (Bait, Sturdy, Huge Calves, added to Soldier for an impressive 36 health), and caps it off with Last Mohican, Charge, Fists of Fury and Frag Grenade.

He really only needs a better rifle to make him a monster, since he only has the Sniper. I won our last fight because he only came in with one in the pipe and one in the clip, and I lived through those. Plus he didn't Charge me, which would have ended it right there.

Kompera

You're not losing much not having Dodger.

Take a look at our last fight:
http://the-solo.minitroopers.com/b/fv...

I'm using a 100 Aim weapon, I have Eye of the Tiger for +50 to Aim. So whatever my Troopers innate Aim number is, I've got 150% of that. You have Bait for some undisclosed amount of being "easier to hit" which further increases my total Aim (or reduces your Dodge? The wiki reads kind of weird on this.) And I still missed you 3 times, and your Tuck'n'Roll went off 2 times. This was out of 10 total shots fired.

So a 30% miss number, and a 20% Tuck'n'Roll activation.

We know from the Compensator that there is an "aiming penalty for successive shots", which to me reads as though the penalties only apply to the second shot and any after it. Even so, to me 3 misses out of 10 seems high for a Trooper with a significantly high Aim number.
